track_notes: This was my track, there are shorter ways to the top but this one has a nice secluded parking spot off the main road, and the route is generally easy with only a short section of semi-steep climbing.  One thing to note, there are dead trees standing in the area.  While I was sitting at the summit and making contacts, the wind actually blew an entire 40-foot pine tree completely down, right next to me...if I had been 10 feet over, I would not have survived to be writing this.  So from now on I will be very, very cautious not to set up where there is a chance that a tree may fall.  There are plenty of spots on this summit that are not in the danger zone of a tree fall.  Overall a nice easy hike and a nice summit.
